Converts the input entity path from a path that is defined relative to the active target object to an "absolute" path that begins with the parent file of the target object. It is assumed that the entity path is an evaluated (i.e. non-persistent) entity path. For example: If the input EntPath's Id[0] = -1, such as Id = { -1, COMP, COMP, FACE}; the output EntPath's Id = { -2, PART, COMP, PART COMP, PART, FACE};
EntPath entity path
evxErrors cvxEntPathToRoot(svxEntPath *EntPath)

This function sets the selection mode of a tree widget.
form form name
field field number
mode tree view control selection mode 

 0: No selection; 

 1: Single selection; 

 2: Multiple selection; 

 3: Extended selection; 

 4: Contiguous selection
evxErrors cvxTreeSetSelectionMode(const char *form, int field, int mode)
